R Markdown

This is an R Markdown document. Markdown is a simple formatting syntax for authoring HTML, PDF, and MS Word documents. For more details on using R Markdown see http://rmarkdown.rstudio.com.

When you click the Knit button a document will be generated that includes both content as well as the output of any embedded R code chunks within the document. You can embed an R code chunk like this:

summary(cars)
##      speed           dist       
##  Min.   : 4.0   Min.   :  2.00  
##  1st Qu.:12.0   1st Qu.: 26.00  
##  Median :15.0   Median : 36.00  
##  Mean   :15.4   Mean   : 42.98  
##  3rd Qu.:19.0   3rd Qu.: 56.00  
##  Max.   :25.0   Max.   :120.00

Including Plots

You can also embed plots, for example:

Note that the echo = FALSE parameter was added to the code chunk to prevent printing of the R code that generated the plot.

qqnorm(Data$adult_weight)
qqline(Data$adult_weight)

shapiro.test(Data$adult_weight)
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  Data$adult_weight
## W = 0.46871, p-value < 2.2e-16
log10AW = log10(Data$adult_weight)
qqnorm(log10AW)
qqline(log10AW)

shapiro.test(log10AW)
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  log10AW
## W = 0.97312, p-value = 0.01733
sqAW = sqrt(Data$adult_weight)
shapiro.test(sqAW)
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  sqAW
## W = 0.6713, p-value = 5.848e-15
shapiro.test(log10AW)

##random assignment of shape
ggplot(Data, aes(y=NeoplasiaPrevalence*100, x=adult_weight)) + scale_x_continuous(trans = 'log10')+
  scale_color_manual(values = c("Mammalia" = "#EE0000FF", "Sauropsida"= "#008b45ff", "Amphibia"= "#3B4992ff" ))+
  geom_abline() +
  theme_cowplot(12)+
  ylab("Neoplasia Prevalence (%)") +
  xlab("(log 10) Adult Weight (g)") +
  geom_point(aes(colour= Clade, shape = Clade)) +
  geom_text_repel(aes(label=ifelse((NeoplasiaPrevalence > 0.4) | NeoplasiaPrevalence < .01,as.character(Species),'')))+
  labs(title = "Neoplasia Prevalence vs. Adult Weight")+
  theme(legend.position = "none")

ggplot(Data, aes(y=NeoplasiaPrevalence*100, x=adult_weight)) + scale_x_continuous(trans = 'log10')+
